mdq:explanation.gco:CharacterString: The vertical accuracy associated with the contours is such that 95% of "well defined" points along the contour line have a value that must not differ to the "true" ground surface by any more then half of the contour interval.
The horizontal accuracy for both the DEM and contour datasets is +/-35cm or better.

The contours are consistent for contour interval, smoothness, cartographic display and elevation attribution.
Logical consistency is a measure of the degree to which data complies with the technical specification. The test procedures include a mixture of scripts and on-screen visual checks.
The extent covers the major flood plains and Greater Melbourne. It does not include products available in Vicmap Elevation - Coastal 1m DEM & 0.5m Contours.

mri:abstract.gco:CharacterString:
Obsolete, the Vicmap DTM 10M product has been significantly updated with new and revised content. and renamed to VICMAP_ELEV_DEM_10.
Vicmap Elevation DTM 10m is a product which is a raster representation of Victoria's elevation. DTM 10m has a spatial resolution of 10m. The DTM is constructed from source data of various resolutions, accuracies and ages to produce an improved DTM containing increased detail in localised areas. The DTMs are hydrologically enforced and correctly defines the natural surface drainage and hydrological flow.

mco:useLimitation.gco:CharacterString: Available directly from Vicmap Data Service Providers listed at www.delwp.vic.gov.au/vicmapdsp or DataVic www.data.vic.gov.au

mdq:explanation.gco:CharacterString: The vertical accuracy associated with the DTMs is +/-5m or better. Reprojecting, changing format or resampling causes changes to the height values in the DTM.

The spatial accuracy for Vicmap Elevation DTM 10m is inherited from the spatial accuracies of its many source datasets. The most consistently used and therefore the base for positional accuracy is the Vicmap Elevation 10-20 Contours & Relief, therefore the positional accuracy for Vicmap Elevation DTM 10m is 12.5m horizontally and 5m vertically or better.
The DTM values across initial basin tiles have been constructed to ensure smooth consistent elevation values is achieved.

Vicmap Elevation DTM 10m has partial coverage over Victoria's main landmass . Please see the product description for a map showing the extent. DTMs have only been generated for islands with sufficient elevation data available to support the DTM 10m product.
